<promed@promedmail.org>
[Dengue is a disease that clearly has emerged. It is now found in
essentially all tropical and many subtropical areas of the world, either as
an endemic and persistent disease or as an endemic and irregularly detected
disease. This Paraguayan situation is reported here because of the obvious
risk for dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) there. For DHF to develop, the
usual situation is that a preceding epidemic caused by a different dengue
virus occurred in that same area. This indicates a persistent, not a new,
vector/virus [albeit a different dengue virus relationship and
demonstrates that in the past inadequate steps had been taken to rid the
place of the vector. Altogether too common in too many places these days. -
Mod. CHC
